title: List Of Applications and Department Partners Using Login.Gov For Identity Management

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

A list of applications and department partners currently using login.gov in production for identity management, applications and partners that have communicated to GSA or the Login.gov project the intent to use login.gov as an identity provider but are not yet in production (ie still in development, testing, QA, etc), and any publicly available URLs where this information is already available on partners.login.gov.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Brandon Galbraith

communications.subject: Wisconsin Open Records Act Request: Waukesha School District: Threats over 'Rainbowland'
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Any recording or copy of the "phone calls and emails, many of which were threatening and vulgar in nature" referenced by the School District of Waukesha in its motion to dismiss the claims in Tempel v. School District of Waukesha, et al., No. 2:23-cv-01169 (E.D. Wis. Nov. 1, 2023).

2. Copies of any police incident report concerning threats, harassment, or increased security related to the 'Rainbowland' controversy.

3. Any other records otherwise related to the "increase[d] security and police presence at the school" referenced by the motion to dismiss in Tempel v. School District of Waukesha.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh
